{
  "texts": [
    "It also includes front-end and back-end operations such as tracking, feature extraction, and matching, which yield an accurate state estimation.",
    "The second stage involves robust pose graph optimization (Kimera-RPGO), tasked with optimization and the formulation of a global trajectory.",
    "Subsequently, the third stage features the per-frame and multi-frame 3D mesh generator (Kimera-Mesher), responsible for the execution and generation of 3D meshes representing the environment.",
    "The fourth stage introduces semantically annotated 3D meshes (Kimera-Semantics), dedicated to generating 3D meshes with semantic annotations.",
    "This stage sets the groundwork for the subsequent and final stage, where the generated 3D meshes are utilized for output visualization, ultimately serving SLAM purposes, as illustrated in Figure 5, part 9."
  ]
}